description:
&lt;p&gt;37.5 hours per week and 35 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Appointments Booking Centre, which is based in Morriston Hospital. The Appointment Office deals with over 10000 calls a month from patients relating to queries regarding their appointments and waiting times. The Appointment Office books patient appointments and supports other areas of the Health Board.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will need to be able to provide a patient centered approach to booking, whilst following guidelines. The candidate will need to be enthusiastic and have good administrative qualities.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be responsible for booking and maintaining clinics and ensuring patients are booked correctly. The post holder will be responsible for updating basic spread sheets and undertake requests for appointments from other departments in the Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours of work 9:00 - 17:00 with one evening shift of 12:00 - 20:00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameRachel HolmesJob titleAppointments Office ManagerEmail addressrachel.holmes@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
